OL,3,CCouncil tax in Scottish Borders to
OL,4,Crise by 8.5%
OL,6,F"We will also continue to maintain our
OL,7,Froads, invest in transport, and
OL,8,Fmaintain teacher numbers."
OL,10,FSNP councillors were accused of
OL,11,F'playing politics' when they walked
OL,12,Fout of talks and attempted to push
OL,13,Fthrough a last minute amendment.
OL,15,FThe opposition, led by Cllr Elaine
OL,16,FThornton-Nicol, instead suggested a 7
OL,17,Fper cent rise in council tax to avoid
OL,18,Fadding extra pressure on already
OL,19,Fstrained household budgets.
